ZH: 我的战友们都很勇敢。
EN: My comrades are all very brave.

ZH: 他是我的战友，我们一起打仗。
EN: He is my comrade, we fight together.

ZH: 我们曾经是同一个连的战友。
EN: We used to be comrades in the same platoon.

ZH: 在军营里，战友之间的友情很重要。
EN: In the military camp, comradeship is very important.

ZH: 我的战友一直支持我，让我感到很安心。
EN: My comrades have always supported me, making me feel very secure.

ZH: 在军事训练中，与战友之间的默契非常重要。
EN: In military training, teamwork with comrades is crucial.

ZH: 她是我最亲密的战友之一。
EN: She is one of my closest comrades.

ZH: 他是我无论什么时候都能依靠的战友。
EN: He is the comrade I can always rely on.

ZH: 我们之间的战友关系已经建立多年。
EN: The comradery between us has been established for many years.

ZH: 和战友一起训练让我觉得更有动力。
EN: Training with comrades gives me more motivation.

ZH: 在战场上，我能信任我的战友们。
EN: On the battlefield, I can trust my comrades.

ZH: 和战友们一起度过的时光让我铭记终生。
EN: The time I spent with my comrades will always be remembered.

ZH: 在部队里，战友之间的友情是铁的。
EN: In the army, the comradeship between comrades is strong.

ZH: 战友之间的默契是战胜敌人的关键。
EN: The teamwork between comrades is the key to defeating the enemy.

ZH: 在危机时刻，我知道我的战友们会站在我身后支持我。
EN: In times of crisis, I know my comrades will stand behind me and support me.

ZH: 战友之间共同战斗，相互保护。
EN: Comrades fight together and protect each other.

ZH: 我的战友们是我生命中最珍贵的人。
EN: My comrades are the most precious people in my life.

ZH: 和这些战友一起工作是我最大的幸运。
EN: Working with these comrades is my greatest fortune.

ZH: 每一个战友都是不可或缺的。
EN: Each comrade is indispensable.

ZH: 我感到非常幸运能有这么伟大的战友。
EN: I feel very lucky to have such great comrades.
